<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 27 at 7:38AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Patchy Black Ice Possible through Mid Morning...
With temperatures hovering near the freezing mark, patches of
black ice will remain possible through mid morning across portions
of the southern Adirondacks, Mohawk Valley, Lake George Saratoga
region, eastern Catskills and Helderbergs, southern Vermont and
higher elevations in the Berkshires.
Untreated secondary roadways will be most prone to patches of
black ice. Motorists and pedestrians should remain vigilant to
locally slippery travel conditions through mid morning across the
areas.</description>
